        Stop In stores sold to Pennsylvania company
    


By Jeff Sturgeon | The Roanoke Times











Jeff Sturgeon


























May 2, 2014
 (…)


























































































A publicly traded Pennsylvania motor fuel distributor has paid $61 million for the Roanoke-based convenience store chain Stop In Food Stores and a related petroleum distributorship.Lehigh Gas Partners LP said Friday its purchase of Petroleum Marketers Inc., which closed Wednesday, will broaden its presence in the Interstate 81 corridor, where PMI operates most of its 85 stores.No employment-related information was released. Messages left for executives at PMI’s Ogden Road office and at Lehigh Gas headquarters in Allentown, Pennsylvania, weren’t returned by late afternoon.Petroleum Marketers incorporated on March 27, 1950, its website says. In addition to operating 40 stores in the Roanoke and New River valleys decked with red, white and blue signs, the company has donated money to educational and health-related causes.A brief profile of PMI supplied in a news release said company stores sold 91 million gallons of motor vehicle fuel and collected $93 million in non-fuel revenue in 2013. The stores will stay open, Lehigh Gas said.PMI, which also delivers petroleum products, distributed 191 million gallons of motor vehicle fuel and lubricants in Virginia, West Virginia, Tennessee and North Carolina last year, the release said.
Lehigh Gas, whose focus is wholesale distribution of motor fuel and retail real estate, earned $18 million on revenue of $1.93 billion in 2013, according to filings.The partnership, which is only about two years old, distributes fuel to more than 1,100 locations and owns or leases 625 fuel stores in 14 states including Virginia. In Virginia, the Lehigh’s owned and leased store locations are concentrated in Richmond. The only one in the Roanoke and New River valleys is the Radford Travel Center on Tyler Road.







Contact Jeff Sturgeon at jeff.sturgeon@roanoke.com or 981-3251. 
























































Jeff Sturgeon

Jeff Sturgeon covers the transportation, banking and federal court beats. Contact Jeff at (540) 981-3251 or jeff.sturgeon@roanoke.com. To send something by mail: 201 W. Campbell Ave., Roanoke, VA 24011.



















